<worksheet label="ws-act-5-2-2">
   
    <activity xml:id="act-5-2-2" workspace="3cm">
      <introduction>
        <p>
          Suppose that <m>f(t) = \frac{t}{1+t^2}</m>. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Note that while we know a function whose derivative is <m>\frac{1}{1+t^2}</m>, namely <m>\arctan(t)</m>,
          we haven't yet encountered an elementary function whose derivative is <m>f(t) = \frac{t}{1+t^2}</m>.
        </p>        
        <p>
          Let <m>F(x) = \int_0^x f(t) \, dt</m>.  We will explore <m>F(x)</m> from numerical, graphical, and algebraic perspectives.  
        </p>
        <!-- <p/>
        <figure xml:id="F-5-2-Act2">
